        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(cron): cron job management improvements — edit, run history, pipeline orchestration (#6808)",
        "body": "Closes #6808\n\n## What changed\n\n### 1. Edit existing cron jobs (bug fixes)\n- Fixed hardcoded English strings in `validateCronForm` — failure alert\n  threshold and cooldown errors now use i18n keys so they render\n  correctly in all locales.\n- Fixed missing `/* @vitest-environment jsdom */` pragma on `cron.test.ts`\n  that caused `ReferenceError: document is not defined` when run under\n  the root Vitest config.\n- Fixed `Run if due` button text — was hardcoded English, now uses\n  `t(\"cron.jobList.runIfDue\")`.\n\n### 2. View execution history (i18n + test registration)\n- Added three cron test files to the root `vitest.config.ts` include\n  list so they actually run in CI:\n  `ui/src/ui/views/cron.test.ts`,\n  `ui/src/ui/controllers/cron.test.ts`,\n  `ui/src/ui/controllers/cron-filters.test.ts`\n- Added i18n keys for `runIfDue`, `failureAlertAfterInvalid`, and\n  `failureAlertCooldownInvalid` in en / es / zh-CN.\n- Added regression test confirming error keys are i18n strings (not raw English).\n\n### 3. Pipeline orchestration — job chaining ✨\nChain cron jobs together: when a job finishes it can automatically\ntrigger another job by ID, based on whether it succeeded or failed.\n\n**Backend (`src/`)**\n- `CronJobBase` gains `onSuccessJobId?: string` and `onFailureJobId?: string`.\n- Gateway schema (`CronCommonOptionalFields`, `CronJobSchema`) exposes\n  the new fields for `cron.add`, `cron.update`, and list/status responses.\n- `timer.ts` enqueues the chained job via `CommandLane.Cron` after each\n  scheduled or manual run; guards against self-loops; uses a lazy\n  `import('./ops.js')` to avoid a circular dependency.\n\n**Web UI (`ui/`)**\n- `CronFormState` and `DEFAULT_CRON_FORM` carry `onSuccessJobId` /\n  `onFailureJobId` string fields.\n- `jobToForm` reads the fields from an existing job when editing.\n- `addCronJob` sends `onSuccessJobId` / `onFailureJobId` (null to clear).\n- Advanced form section gains a **Pipeline** subsection with two\n  job-ID text inputs backed by a `<datalist>` of all known jobs for\n  autocomplete.\n- i18n keys in en / es / zh-CN.\n\n## Test plan\n- [x] All 59 cron unit tests pass (`pnpm test -- ui/src/ui/...`)\n- [x] oxlint: 0 warnings / 0 errors on all changed files\n- [x] oxfmt: all changed files formatted correctly\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)",
